The University of Michigan has announced Santa Ono, former president of the University of British Columbia, as their new president. In honor of his appointment, the university has cancelled all final exams for the current semester, prompting mixed reactions from students. Plans for a special event to celebrate Ono's arrival are also underway. There is hope that his tenure will bring positive changes to the university, with a focus on student well-being and diversity. The campus is currently buzzing with excitement and anticipation for the future.
